---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteFooter from "../components/SiteFooter.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Snap311"
  description="What Snap311 collects, what it doesn't, and the third parties involved when you file a DC 311 report."
>
  <!-- Header band -->
  <header class="bg-cream">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-14 sm:py-20">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm font-semibold text-brand underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-navy"
      >
        <span aria-hidden="true">←</span> Back to Snap311
      </a>

      <h1
        class="mt-6 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-navy-deep sm:text-5xl"
      >
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-muted">
        Last updated: June 16, 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="bg-white">
    <div
      class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-10 px-6 py-14 text-base leading-relaxed text-ink sm:py-20"
    >
      <p>
        Snap311 ("the app") is an independent, unofficial mobile client for
        filing service requests with the District of Columbia 311 system. The
        app is not affiliated with or endorsed by the DC Office of Unified
        Communications or any DC government agency.
      </p>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-navy-deep">
          What we collect
        </h2>
        <p>
          Snap311 collects only what's needed to file a service request and to
          make the app work reliably:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>Contact info you enter</strong> (first/last name, email or
              phone). Stored locally on your device using iOS encrypted storage.
              Sent to DC's official 311 API at <code
                class="rounded bg-black/5 px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm text-ink/80"
                >dc311-api.herokuapp.com</code
              > only when you submit a report.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>Address and location data</strong> for the report you're
              filing. Extracted from the GPS in your chosen photo's EXIF
              metadata, or typed by you, or picked on a map. Sent to DC's 311 API
              as part of the report.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>Photos you choose to attach.</strong> Uploaded to DC's
              official 311 worker at <code
                class="rounded bg-black/5 px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm text-ink/80"
                >dc311-api-worker.herokuapp.com</code
              >, which stores them in DC's Salesforce system as part of the
              service request.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>Diagnostic / crash reports</strong> (optional, can be
              disabled). Sentry SDK events about errors and slow API calls,
              scrubbed of API keys and personal data. Used only to fix bugs. You
              can disable this in <strong>Settings → Send diagnostics</strong>.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-navy-deep">
          What we do NOT collect
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>We do not track your location in the background.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>We do not sell, share, or monetize any of your data.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              We do not use advertising SDKs or third-party trackers (no Google
              Analytics, Meta SDK, etc.).
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-muted"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              We do not require an account with us. There is no Snap311 account;
              your contact info stays on your device and is only attached to the
              reports you submit to DC.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-navy-deep">
          Third parties
        </h2>
        <p>When you submit a report, the data you've entered is sent to:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>DC's official 311 API</strong> (<code
                class="rounded bg-black/5 px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm text-ink/80"
                >dc311-api.herokuapp.com</code
              >) — the same backend the official DC 311 app and 311.dc.gov web
              portal use. Their handling of your data is governed by DC
              government policy.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>DC's official 311 worker</strong> (<code
                class="rounded bg-black/5 px-1 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm text-ink/80"
                >dc311-api-worker.herokuapp.com</code
              >) — for photo attachments, stored in DC's Salesforce.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>If you opt in (or leave on by default) to diagnostics:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>Sentry</strong> (sentry.io) — receives error reports with
              breadcrumbs of what you did right before the error. API keys are
              scrubbed before send. Personal info (name, email, contact info) is
              never sent. You can disable any time.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-navy-deep">
          Your choices
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>Disable diagnostics</strong>: Settings → Send diagnostics →
              off.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>Remove your saved info</strong>: Delete the app. Local
              storage is erased with the app on iOS.
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span
              class="mt-2 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-brand"
              aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>
              <strong>Remove a submitted report</strong>: Snap311 can't do this —
              submissions live in DC's Salesforce system after you file. Contact
              DC 311 directly to request a record correction.
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-navy-deep">
          Children
        </h2>
        <p>
          Snap311 is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly
          collect personal information from children.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-navy-deep">
          Changes
        </h2>
        <p>
          If this policy changes materially, the new version will be posted at <a
            href="https://snap311.app/privacy"
            class="text-brand underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-navy"
            >snap311.app/privacy</a
          > with an updated date. Continued use after a change indicates
          acceptance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-navy-deep">
          Contact
        </h2>
        <p>
          Open an issue: <a
            href="https://github.com/kfiducia/snap311-policy/issues"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-brand underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-navy"
            >github.com/kfiducia/snap311-policy/issues</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <SiteFooter />
</Layout>
